# naapp stack conventions

## Test data

- Use known tenant snapshots in `framework/data/tenantSnapshot.ts` with a pinned snapshot version.
- GraphQL stub payloads live in `framework/data/graphqlFixtures.ts` and should be checked with TypeScript types when schema codegen is wired.

## GraphQL

- Typed operations go in `framework/api/operations/`.
- Stub via `framework/mocks/graphqlMock.ts` (`page.route` wrapper), not MSW.
- Refresh types with the `regen-graphql-types` command against the stage2 schema.

## Auth

- REST login in `setup/auth.setup.ts` seeds `.auth/user.json` (`storageState`).
- UI login is tested directly only in dedicated smoke coverage, not repeated per spec.

## Feature flags

- Pin critical GrowthBook flags in fixtures for deterministic smoke runs.

## Component catalog

- Pull `component-catalog.json` from naapp CI-published artifacts by version/tag.
- Cache during the test run; fall back to a committed copy for offline runs.
- E2E validates deterministic render-spec consumption; LLM quality evals stay in backend deepeval/MLflow.
